'''Mohamed Ibrahim Abdullah Kanno''' ({{langx|ar|محمد إبراهيم عبد الله كنو}}; born 22 September 1994) is a Saudi Arabian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Saudi Pro League]] club [[Al Hilal SFC|Al Hilal]] and the [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia national team]].

==Club career==
===Ettifaq===
Kanno was playing at [[Al-Ettifaq Club|Ettifaq]] in 2013–2017, who were relegated in 2014. In 2016, Kanno helped his team get back into the league. He left in 2017 to join [[Al Hilal SFC|Al-Hilal]].

===Al-Hilal===
On 3 July 2017, Kanno moved to [[Al-Hilal FC|Al-Hilal]] on a five-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://m.kooora.com/?n=601228|title=كووورة: الموقع العربي الرياضي الأول|date=9 July 2019|access-date=4 July 2017|archive-date=12 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612143003/http://m.kooora.com/?n=601228|url-status=live}}</ref>

==International career==
In May 2018, he was named in Saudi Arabia's preliminary [[Saudi Arabia national football team|squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/440833652018|title=World Cup 2018: All the confirmed squads for this summer's finals in Russia}}{{dead link|date=September 2025|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>

At the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], he started all three group stage matches for Saudi Arabia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.besoccer.com/match/seleccion-argentina/seleccion-arabia-saudi/2022445096/lineups|title=BeSoccer: Argentina vs Saudi Arabia lineups|access-date=6 January 2023|archive-date=6 January 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230106225626/https://www.besoccer.com/match/seleccion-argentina/seleccion-arabia-saudi/2022445096/lineups|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.besoccer.com/match/seleccion-polonia/seleccion-arabia-saudi/2022445098/lineups|title=BeSoccer: Poland vs Saudi Arabia lineups|access-date=6 January 2023|archive-date=6 January 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230106225636/https://www.besoccer.com/match/seleccion-polonia/seleccion-arabia-saudi/2022445098/lineups|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.besoccer.com/match/seleccion-arabia-saudi/seleccion-mexico/2022445100|title=BeSoccer: Saudi Arabia vs Mexico lineups|access-date=6 January 2023|archive-date=6 January 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230106225626/https://www.besoccer.com/match/seleccion-arabia-saudi/seleccion-mexico/2022445100|url-status=live}}</ref> Despite defeating eventual champion [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] in their first match, Saudi Arabia finished fourth in their group and did not advance to the knockout stage.

